    "translationHint": "A gentleman is as firm as a stone in the middle of water, and others fear his aloofness; few will not mistake a precious pearl for an oddity and raise their swords in suspicion. A petty person is as slick as grease, and people delight in how easily they can be won over; few will not take poison as sweet honey and indulge their desires with reckless fingers.",
    "tags": []
