    "translationHint": "A dragon that can be tamed is not a true dragon; a tiger that can be subdued is not a real tiger. Therefore, titles and wealth may entice those who seek honor and advancement, but they certainly cannot ensnare one who remains detached and free of desire. A cauldron or kettle might reach those who chase favor and profit, but it surely cannot touch the man who has already withdrawn far away with an unbound spirit.",
